cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a method for optimizing geometric constellation shapes to improve the GMI (Generalized Mutual Information) metric, which is a fundamental concept in information theory.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the proposed method uses autoencoders for shaping and optimizing bit mappings, which are machine learning techniques.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper discusses the impact of transceiver impairments on the performance of the proposed method, which is relevant to networking and communication systems.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a method for optimizing the performance of a communication system, which can be seen as a control problem.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the proposed method can be applied to improve the performance of multimedia communication systems that use constellation shaping.
